      "Bash(git push:*)",
      "Bash(--title \"PM-081: To-Do Lists as Core Domain Objects\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"## Story\nAs a PM using Piper, I want to-do lists to be first-class domain objects so I can create, manage, and track structured task lists with AI assistance and cross-platform integration.\n\n## Context\nTo-do lists are fundamental PM artifacts that currently exist only as text. Elevating them to core domain objects would enable:\n- Sophisticated task management and tracking\n- AI-guided task breakdown and execution\n- Natural integration with GitHub issues/checklists, Jira tasks, etc.\n- Perfect structure for agent guidance through complex workflows\n\n## Strategic Value\n1. **Universal PM Pattern**: Every PM works with task lists across multiple tools\n2. **Agent Guidance**: Structured tasks provide clear execution paths for AI\n3. **Integration Hub**: Natural translation point between different PM tools\n4. **Differentiation**: Positions Piper as intelligent task orchestration layer\n\n## Proposed Domain Models\n\\`\\`\\`python\n@dataclass\nclass TaskList:\n    id: str\n    name: str\n    description: Optional[str]\n    project_id: Optional[str]  # Links to existing projects\n    owner_id: str\n    tasks: List[TaskItem]\n    created_at: datetime\n    updated_at: Optional[datetime]\n    status: TaskListStatus  # ACTIVE, COMPLETED, ARCHIVED\n    source: Optional[str]  # github, manual, ai_generated\n\n@dataclass\nclass TaskItem:\n    id: str\n    title: str\n    description: Optional[str]\n    parent_id: Optional[str]  # For subtasks\n    dependencies: List[str]  # Other task IDs\n    status: TaskStatus  # TODO, IN_PROGRESS, DONE, BLOCKED\n    assigned_to: Optional[str]\n    due_date: Optional[datetime]\n    external_refs: Dict[str, str]  # {\"\"github_issue\"\": \"\"123\"\"}\n    metadata: Dict[str, Any]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Key Features\n- [ ] Create/manage hierarchical task lists\n- [ ] Track task completion and progress\n- [ ] AI-assisted task breakdown from high-level goals\n- [ ] Bidirectional sync with GitHub issues/checklists\n- [ ] Slack commands for task management\n- [ ] Dependency tracking and blocking\n- [ ] Progress analytics and insights\n\n## Integration Points\n- **GitHub**: Epic → Issues → Checklists mapping\n- **Slack**: Natural language task commands\n- **Workflows**: Tasks can trigger workflows\n- **Spatial Intelligence**: Task priority as attention weight\n\n## Success Criteria\n- [ ] Domain models implemented and tested\n- [ ] Basic CRUD operations working\n- [ ] GitHub issue checklist sync\n- [ ] Slack command integration\n- [ ] AI can break down high-level goals into tasks\n\n## Estimate\nInitial MVP: 21-34 points\nFull implementation with integrations: 55+ points\n\n## Dependencies\n- Core domain model stability\n- GitHub integration patterns established\n- Slack integration operational\n\n## Related\n- Potential integration with OneJob (PM''s task management UI)\n- Enhancement to existing Project/Goal management\n- Foundation for future workflow automation\n\n## Questions to Resolve\n1. How do TaskLists relate to existing Projects?\n2. Should tasks be immutable once created?\n3. How deep should subtask nesting go?\n4. What''s the sync strategy for external changes?\n\n**Priority**: P2 (High value, build after foundation complete)\n**Milestone**: Phase 3 - Enhanced Intelligence\" )",
      "Bash(ls:*)",
      "Bash(cat:*)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/unit/test_query_response_formatter.py -v)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/unit/test_query_response_formatter.py::TestQueryResponseFormatter::test_is_degradation_response_string -v)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/integration/test_query_router_system_degradation.py::TestQueryRouterSystemDegradation::test_cascade_failure_prevention -v)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/unit/test_query_response_formatter.py tests/integration/test_query_router_system_degradation.py -v --tb=short)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/integration/test_query_router_system_degradation.py::TestQueryRouterSystemDegradation::test_individual_query_degradation -v)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/queries/test_query_router_degradation.py -v)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/integration/test_api_degradation_integration.py -v)",
      "Bash(PYTHONPATH=. python -m pytest tests/integration/test_query_router_system_degradation.py -v)",
