      "Bash(--title \"SITE-001: Technical Foundation & Architecture Setup\" )",
      "Bash(--label \"website,sprint-01,P0-critical\" )",
      "Bash(--milestone \"Website MVP\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"**Priority**: P0 - Critical Path\n**Estimate**: 8 points\n**Agent Assignment**: Claude Code (High Context)\n\n## Description\nEstablish the technical foundation for pipermorgan.ai website following Domain-Driven Design principles. Create the domain model for website content, set up Next.js with static site generation, and establish the deployment pipeline.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Domain model created for website content (pages, components, integrations)\n- [ ] Next.js project initialized in \\`site/\\` directory with TypeScript\n- [ ] Static site generation configured for performance\n- [ ] Build pipeline established (dev, build, export commands)\n- [ ] Deployment configuration for Vercel/Netlify\n- [ ] Basic routing structure for 5 pages (Home, About, Newsletter, Blog, How It Works)\n- [ ] Component architecture following atomic design principles\n- [ ] Performance baseline established (Lighthouse CI integration)\n\n## Domain Model Requirements\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\n// Core domain entities\ninterface WebsiteContent {\n  pages: Page[]\n  components: Component[]\n  integrations: Integration[]\n}\n\ninterface Page {\n  slug: string\n  title: string\n  description: string\n  components: Component[]\n  seoMetadata: SEOMetadata\n}\n\ninterface Integration {\n  type: ''convertkit'' | ''medium'' | ''analytics''\n  configuration: IntegrationConfig\n  status: ''active'' | ''inactive''\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Technical Specifications\n- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ with App Router\n- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom design system\n- **Performance**: Static site generation for all pages\n- **SEO**: Built-in metadata API and sitemap generation\n- **Testing**: Jest + Testing Library for component testing\n\n## Success Criteria\n- All builds pass without errors\n- Basic page routing functional\n- Performance: Lighthouse score >85 on initial setup\n- Domain models clearly defined and documented\n- Ready for parallel component development\")",
      "Bash(--title \"SITE-001: Technical Foundation & Architecture Setup\" )",
      "Bash(--label \"website,sprint-01,P0-critical\" )",
      "Bash(--milestone \"Website MVP\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"**Priority**: P0 - Critical Path\n**Estimate**: 8 points\n**Agent Assignment**: Claude Code (High Context)\n\n## Description\nEstablish the technical foundation for pipermorgan.ai website following Domain-Driven Design principles. Create the domain model for website content, set up Next.js with static site generation, and establish the deployment pipeline.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Domain model created for website content (pages, components, integrations)\n- [ ] Next.js project initialized in \\`site/\\` directory with TypeScript\n- [ ] Static site generation configured for performance\n- [ ] Build pipeline established (dev, build, export commands)\n- [ ] Deployment configuration for Vercel/Netlify\n- [ ] Basic routing structure for 5 pages (Home, About, Newsletter, Blog, How It Works)\n- [ ] Component architecture following atomic design principles\n- [ ] Performance baseline established (Lighthouse CI integration)\n\n## Domain Model Requirements\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\n// Core domain entities\ninterface WebsiteContent {\n  pages: Page[]\n  components: Component[]\n  integrations: Integration[]\n}\n\ninterface Page {\n  slug: string\n  title: string\n  description: string\n  components: Component[]\n  seoMetadata: SEOMetadata\n}\n\ninterface Integration {\n  type: ''convertkit'' | ''medium'' | ''analytics''\n  configuration: IntegrationConfig\n  status: ''active'' | ''inactive''\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Technical Specifications\n- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ with App Router\n- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with custom design system\n- **Performance**: Static site generation for all pages\n- **SEO**: Built-in metadata API and sitemap generation\n- **Testing**: Jest + Testing Library for component testing\n\n## Success Criteria\n- All builds pass without errors\n- Basic page routing functional\n- Performance: Lighthouse score >85 on initial setup\n- Domain models clearly defined and documented\n- Ready for parallel component development\")",
      "Bash(--title \"SITE-002: Design System & Component Library\" )",
      "Bash(--label \"website,sprint-01,P0-critical\" )",
      "Bash(--milestone \"Website MVP\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"**Priority**: P0 - Critical Path\n**Estimate**: 5 points\n**Agent Assignment**: Cursor Agent (Limited Context)\n\n## Description\nImplement the design system foundation based on established brand guidelines. Create reusable UI components following the teal-orange palette and professional aesthetic established in strategic planning.\n\n## MANDATORY VERIFICATION FIRST\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# Check existing patterns\nfind site/ -name \"\"*.css\"\" -o -name \"\"*.scss\"\" -o -name \"\"*.module.css\"\"\ngrep -r \"\"color\\|font\\|spacing\"\" site/ --include=\"\"*.ts\"\" --include=\"\"*.tsx\"\"\ncat site/tailwind.config.js 2>/dev/null || echo \"\"No Tailwind config found\"\"\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Design tokens implemented (colors, typography, spacing)\n- [ ] Component library structure established\n- [ ] Core components built: Header, Footer, Hero, CTAButton, NewsletterSignup\n- [ ] Tailwind configuration with custom design system\n- [ ] Component documentation with Storybook or similar\n- [ ] Responsive utilities and breakpoints configured\n- [ ] Dark mode considerations (future-ready)\n- [ ] Accessibility standards met (WCAG 2.1 AA)\n\n## Design System Specifications\n\\`\\`\\`css\n:root {\n  --primary-teal: #2DD4BF;\n  --primary-orange: #FB923C;\n  --text-dark: #1F2937;\n  --text-light: #6B7280;\n  --background: #FFFFFF;\n  --surface: #F9FAFB;\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Component Requirements\n- **Atomic Design**: Atoms → Molecules → Organisms → Templates\n- **TypeScript**: Fully typed component props\n- **Testing**: Unit tests for all components\n- **Documentation**: Props tables and usage examples\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Design system matches brand guidelines\n- All components render correctly across breakpoints\n- Lighthouse accessibility score >95\n- Component reusability demonstrated\n- Zero runtime CSS-in-JS for performance\")",
      "Bash(--title \"SITE-004: Integrations & External Services\" )",
      "Bash(--label \"website,sprint-01\" )",
      "Bash(--milestone \"Website MVP\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"**Priority**: P1 - High\n**Estimate**: 5 points\n**Agent Assignment**: Claude Code (Integration Focus)\n\n## Description\nImplement all external service integrations for the pipermorgan.ai website, including ConvertKit for newsletter signups, Medium RSS for blog content, and Google Analytics 4 for tracking.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] ConvertKit form integration with proper error handling\n- [ ] Medium RSS feed parsing and display\n- [ ] Google Analytics 4 setup with event tracking\n- [ ] Environment variable configuration for all services\n- [ ] Fallback strategies for service failures\n- [ ] CORS and security considerations handled\n- [ ] Rate limiting for external API calls\n- [ ] Caching strategy for external content\n\n## Integration Specifications\n\n### ConvertKit Integration\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// Requirements:\n// - Embed form or API integration\n// - Success/error state handling\n// - Thank you page redirect\n// - Double opt-in support\n// - GDPR compliance\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Medium RSS Integration\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// Feed URL: https://medium.com/feed/building-piper-morgan\n// Requirements:\n// - Parse RSS XML to JSON\n// - Extract: title, excerpt, date, link, author\n// - Cache results for 1 hour\n// - Graceful fallback if feed unavailable\n// - Sanitize HTML content\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Google Analytics 4\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// Requirements:\n// - Page view tracking\n// - Newsletter signup events\n// - Blog click-through tracking\n// - Performance metrics\n// - Privacy-compliant implementation\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\\`\\`\\`env\nNEXT_PUBLIC_CONVERTKIT_FORM_ID=xxx\nNEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-xxx\nMEDIUM_RSS_FEED_URL=https://medium.com/feed/building-piper-morgan\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Security Requirements\n- API keys in environment variables only\n- Server-side API calls where possible\n- Content Security Policy headers\n- CORS configuration for allowed domains\n- Input sanitization for form submissions\n\n## Caching Strategy\n- Medium feed: 1-hour cache with stale-while-revalidate\n- Static content: Immutable cache headers\n- API responses: Appropriate cache headers\n\n## Success Criteria\n- All integrations functional in production\n- Zero exposed API keys or secrets\n- Graceful degradation if services unavailable\n- Performance impact <100ms per integration\n- Privacy compliance verified\")",
      "Bash(--title \"SITE-005: Performance, SEO & Launch Readiness\" )",
      "Bash(--label \"website,sprint-01\" )",
      "Bash(--milestone \"Website MVP\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"**Priority**: P1 - High\n**Estimate**: 3 points\n**Agent Assignment**: Cursor Agent (Polish & Optimization)\n\n## Description\nFinal optimization pass for performance, SEO, accessibility, and production deployment readiness. Ensure the website meets all quality standards and is ready for public launch.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Lighthouse scores >90 across all metrics\n- [ ] Cross-browser testing completed (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)\n- [ ] Mobile responsive testing on real devices\n- [ ] SEO technical audit passed\n- [ ] Accessibility audit (WCAG 2.1 AA) passed\n- [ ] Production deployment configuration ready\n- [ ] Domain configuration documented\n- [ ] Launch checklist completed\n\n## Performance Optimization\n- [ ] Bundle size analysis and optimization\n- [ ] Image optimization and lazy loading\n- [ ] Font loading optimization\n- [ ] Critical CSS extraction\n- [ ] JavaScript code splitting\n- [ ] Preconnect to external domains\n- [ ] Service worker for offline support (optional)\n\n## SEO Requirements\n- [ ] Meta tags on all pages\n- [ ] Open Graph tags for social sharing\n- [ ] Twitter Card tags\n- [ ] Canonical URLs\n- [ ] Robots.txt configuration\n- [ ] Sitemap.xml generation\n- [ ] Schema.org markup where applicable\n- [ ] Alt text for all images\n\n## Accessibility Checklist\n- [ ] Keyboard navigation working\n- [ ] Screen reader testing\n- [ ] Color contrast ratios meet WCAG AA\n- [ ] Focus indicators visible\n- [ ] ARIA labels where needed\n- [ ] Skip to content link\n- [ ] Form labels and error messages\n\n## Cross-Browser Testing\n- [ ] Chrome (latest)\n- [ ] Firefox (latest)\n- [ ] Safari (latest)\n- [ ] Edge (latest)\n- [ ] Mobile Safari (iOS)\n- [ ] Chrome Mobile (Android)\n\n## Production Checklist\n- [ ] Environment variables documented\n- [ ] Build process optimized\n- [ ] Error tracking setup (Sentry free tier)\n- [ ] 404 page implemented\n- [ ] Security headers configured\n- [ ] SSL certificate verified\n- [ ] DNS configuration guide prepared\n\n## Deployment Configuration\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\n// Vercel configuration\n{\n  \"\"buildCommand\"\": \"\"npm run build\"\",\n  \"\"outputDirectory\"\": \"\".next\"\",\n  \"\"devCommand\"\": \"\"npm run dev\"\",\n  \"\"framework\"\": \"\"nextjs\"\"\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Launch Verification\n- [ ] All links tested and working\n- [ ] Forms submitting correctly\n- [ ] Analytics tracking verified\n- [ ] Page load times <2s\n- [ ] No console errors in production\n- [ ] Content proofread and approved\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Website ready for public launch\n- All quality metrics exceeded\n- Zero critical issues\n- Deployment process documented\n- Handoff to Christian completed\")",
