      "Bash(PRE_COMMIT_ALLOW_NO_CONFIG=1 git commit -m \"$(cat <<''EOF''\nAdd index.html to fix GitHub Pages 404 error\n\n- Create index.html that redirects to README.md for proper docs serving\n- Resolves \"File not found\" error when accessing pmorgan.tech root URL\n- Includes fallback JavaScript redirect and manual link\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\")",
      "Bash(PRE_COMMIT_ALLOW_NO_CONFIG=1 git commit -m \"$(cat <<''EOF''\nConfigure Jekyll for proper markdown rendering\n\n- Add _config.yml with kramdown markdown processor and GFM support\n- Remove .nojekyll to enable Jekyll processing\n- Update index.html redirects to use ./README (Jekyll will handle .md extension)\n- Enable relative links plugin for proper navigation\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\")",
      "Bash(PRE_COMMIT_ALLOW_NO_CONFIG=1 git commit -m \"$(cat <<''EOF''\nExclude archive directory from Jekyll processing\n\n- Add archive/ to exclude list in _config.yml\n- Resolves Jekyll build failure caused by unclosed {% raw %} tag in archived session logs\n- Archive directory contains session logs not meant for public documentation\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\")",
      "Bash(touch:*)",
      "Bash(PRE_COMMIT_ALLOW_NO_CONFIG=1 git commit -m \"$(cat <<''EOF''\nDisable Jekyll and return to plain markdown serving\n\n- Remove _config.yml and restore .nojekyll to disable Jekyll processing\n- Revert index.html redirects back to ./README.md\n- Resolves Jekyll build failures from unclosed {% raw %} tags in development docs\n- GitHub Pages will serve markdown files directly without Jekyll processing\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\")",
      "Bash(tar:*)",
      "Bash(--title \"PM-087: Values & Principles Architecture - Ethics-First Foundation\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"Implement architectural enforcement of Piper''s ethical boundaries and professional principles. This is foundational infrastructure that must be in place before autonomous capabilities.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] BoundaryEnforcer service intercepts all requests\n- [ ] Professional boundary violations architecturally impossible\n- [ ] Audit trail captures all principle-related decisions\n- [ ] Pattern learning from metadata (not personal content)\n- [ ] Transparent audit logs available to users\n- [ ] All forms of harassment/hostile behavior blocked\n- [ ] Graceful handling with explanations\n\n## Technical Components\n1. services/ethics/boundary_enforcer.py - Core enforcement\n2. services/ethics/adaptive_boundaries.py - Pattern learning\n3. services/ethics/audit_transparency.py - User-visible logs\n4. services/domain/models.py - Add EthicalDecision model\n5. Integration with all request flows\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Boundary enforcement at infrastructure level\n- Pattern learning from interaction metadata\n- Witness vs participant protocols\n- Transparent audit logs with security redactions\n- Protection hierarchy: Human > System > Org > Project\n\nEstimate: 13-21 points | Priority: P0 - Foundational | Dependencies: None\" )",
      "Bash(--label \"ethics,infrastructure,p0,foundational\")",
      "Bash(--title \"PM-087: Values & Principles Architecture - Ethics-First Foundation\" )",
      "Bash(--body \"Implement architectural enforcement of Piper''s ethical boundaries and professional principles. This is foundational infrastructure that must be in place before autonomous capabilities.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] BoundaryEnforcer service intercepts all requests\n- [ ] Professional boundary violations architecturally impossible\n- [ ] Audit trail captures all principle-related decisions\n- [ ] Pattern learning from metadata (not personal content)\n- [ ] Transparent audit logs available to users\n- [ ] All forms of harassment/hostile behavior blocked\n- [ ] Graceful handling with explanations\n\n## Technical Components\n1. services/ethics/boundary_enforcer.py - Core enforcement\n2. services/ethics/adaptive_boundaries.py - Pattern learning\n3. services/ethics/audit_transparency.py - User-visible logs\n4. services/domain/models.py - Add EthicalDecision model\n5. Integration with all request flows\n\n## Implementation Details\n- Boundary enforcement at infrastructure level\n- Pattern learning from interaction metadata\n- Witness vs participant protocols\n- Transparent audit logs with security redactions\n- Protection hierarchy: Human > System > Org > Project\n\nEstimate: 13-21 points | Priority: P0 - Foundational | Dependencies: None\")",
